# HoneyNewsBG

HoneyNewsBG is a news platform that provides the latest articles on various topics. The platform is designed to be visually appealing, user-friendly, and easy to navigate. It supports user authentication and different roles (e.g., Admin) for managing the content.

## Features

- User authentication (Login/Register)
- Admin panel for managing articles
- Responsive design
- Attractive UI with background images and transparent containers
- Latest news articles displayed with summaries and 'Read More' links

## Tech Stack

- ASP.NET Core MVC
- Entity Framework Core
- SQL Server
- Bootstrap 4
- Font Awesome

## Screenshots

![Screenshot](path/to/screenshot.png)

## Getting Started

Follow these instructions to set up the project on your local machine for development and testing purposes.

### Prerequisites

- [.NET Core SDK](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download)
- [SQL Server](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/sql-server/sql-server-downloads)
- [SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS)](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/sql/ssms/download-sql-server-management-studio-ssms)

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**

    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/HoneyNewsBG.git
    cd HoneyNewsBG
    ```

2. **Restore the .NET packages:**

    ```sh
    dotnet restore
    ```

3. **Set up the database:**

    - Open SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS).
    - Connect to your SQL Server instance.
    - Open the `setup.sql` script located in the root directory of the project.
    - Execute the script to create the database schema and populate initial data.

4. **Update the connection string:**

    - Open `appsettings.json`.
    - Update the `ConnectionStrings:DefaultConnection` with your SQL Server connection details.

    ```json
    "ConnectionStrings": {
        "DefaultConnection": "Server=your_server_name;Database=your_database_name;User Id=your_user_id;Password=your_password;"
    }
    ```

5. **Run the application:**

    ```sh
    dotnet run
    ```

6. **Open your browser and navigate to:**

    ```
    http://localhost:5000
    ```

## Usage

- Navigate to the home page to see the latest news articles.
- Use the 'Admin Panel' to manage articles (available only for Admin users).
- Click 'Read More' to view the full article.

